reviews.text: Food is nice, service is typical HK style rush rush.  Buns are all freshly made and served warm.  Love the egg tart.  Curry chicken chop is nice and not too spicy, taste closer to Japanese curry.  Baked seafood rice is served with generous amount of seafood.  Kids friendly.
Best pineapple bun i ever had! came here for lunch while waiting for movie time at langham place. Food is good and affordable

Nice impression upon 1st visit. A true standout from the generic crowd along the same street. It reminds me of the once famous Tsui Wah group at their prime time, especially the items and the menu design.  Haven't had the chance to make a fair comparison but the Ice Bean Fleecy is good enough to be the ❝Pick of the Picky❞.

*Another “+" upon my 2nd visit:  They offer fresh-from-the-oven Breads & Pies, as late as 10pm, which is very very rare❢
One of the best local tea house in town.  Pineapple Bun and the milk tea are signature dishes.
